Dragonmaw Guild<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulordloralon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordLoralon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(7/8/02 4:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.legion-whiterose.com/avatars/legion.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which level 8 spells should I buy?</span><hr size=1> Buy at least 1 pet. Fire may be a little weak, so I'd go Water or Earth.<br>
<br>
Now at Lv8, you get lots of utility spells.<br>
<br>
-dim pocket: well, you can live without it for awhile, but buy it as soon as you can.<br>
<br>
-Eye of zoom: fun spell, only buy it out of boredom or when you gain money in PPs instead of SPs.<br>
<br>
Flame Bolt/shock of blades: I personnally prefer SoB. A must.<br>
<br>
Invisibility: a must have if you plan on doing any travelling at all. If you plan on staying where you are for awhile, you can live without it, but buy it as soon as you can.<br>
<br>
Lesser Shielding: shielding is always good. If you think you can hunt without getting hit too much, you can postpone buying this one.<br>
<br>
Renew elements: I personnally never bought that one, but the upgrade (renew summonning) is a blessing. So I assume you can postpone that one too.<br>
<br>
Shield of Fire: If you buy the Fire pet, and you play solo, no need of this pet. But for any other pet, or for grouping, this is the friend-making spell. Tanks will love you.<br>
<br>
Staff of tracing: Good weapon for your pet, or for you when you'll be hunting will-o-wisps (unless you already have a magical weapon). other than that, no use.<br>
<br>
Linen mantle: buy it to fill in your shoulder slot, is you use the shielding and damage shield spells.<br>
<br>
Malachite: When you zone in to South Felwithe, the door directly in front of you has a couple of vendors. One has our Malachite. <p><center><a href="http://www.legion-whiterose.com"><img src="http://www.legion-whiterose.com/signatures/legionnaires/loralon.jpg"></a><br><i><b>Verba Volant, Scripta Manent</b></i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umuddwinkthistleskin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muddwink Thistleskin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(7/8/02 5:28:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1394.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Which level 8 spells should I buy?</span><hr size=1> At level 8...get a pet spell...either water or earth..as has been stated.  Next I would go for the damage spell...probably the blades one..although you will still want to get fire later on.  With these two spells you should be able to solo the Orc Centurions outside and inside Crushbone.  It's been a while...but I believe the ones outside drop CB belts..just like the ones inside.  These you can either turn in for a quest in the Dwarf City...or you can sell them to other players for PP.  Either way...will be great exp and plat.  By the time you reach lev 10...you should have enough money to buy the rest of your spells.  At early levels...I believe shielding is very beneficial..as you should be tanking for your pet some.  Granted...your pet might not need your help...but I believe its good to get your defensive and offensive abilities up at the lower levels.  Makes life a little easier at higher levels.  Also...some of the summoned weapons you get later on have a right click effect.  These can come in handy from time to time...especially earlier on in your career.....from what I recall..most of them are &quot;insta-click&quot;...meaning no cast time.  Have fun.<br>
<br>
Llassar Wurmburner<br>
Deployed Mage of the 55th Circle<br>
Officer of the Steel Horsemen<br>
<br>
Explosive Ordnance Disposal<br>
<br>
